# Prisma Query Rules

## Always scope by tenantId

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — missing tenant filter, exposes cross-tenant data
prisma.card.findUnique({ where: { id } })

// ✅ GOOD — findFirst with tenantId ensures ownership
prisma.card.findFirst({ where: { id, tenantId } })
```

Never use `findUnique` on an ID alone. Always use `findFirst` with `{ id, tenantId }`.

## Use explicit select — no overfetch

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — returns all fields including sensitive relations
prisma.board.findMany({ where: { tenantId } })

// ✅ GOOD
prisma.board.findMany({
  where: { tenantId },
  select: { id: true, title: true, createdAt: true },
  orderBy: { createdAt: 'desc' },
  take: 50,
})
```

## Cascade ownership checks for nested resources
Before mutating a Card or Lane, verify its parent Board belongs to the tenant:

```typescript
// card.data.ts
const card = await prisma.card.findFirst({
  where: { id: cardId, tenantId },
  include: { lane: { include: { board: true } } },
});
if (!card) throw new NotFoundError('Card not found');
```

## Ordering
Cards and Lanes use integer `position` fields. After a move, use a transaction to update displaced sibling positions. Positions must remain unique per lane.
